main event: A fast-moving UFO was reported over Santa Clara and San Mateo counties on 5 September 1963.
interesting points: Twenty reports were received from the sheriff's offices in Santa Clara and San Mateo counties., The object was described as a half moon pulsating object., Witnesses noted a circular object that was lighted from top to bottom., The light seemed to turn off and on intermittently., The Federal Aviation Agency could not account for the UFO.
witness description: reports from individuals in the area
